<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="198" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1401,2076]" box="[189,1211,1401,1428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1402,1428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The epithet of the new species refers to its common locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[1059,1104,1402,1428]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1158,1207,1402,1428]" name="Iraq" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Iraq</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1401,2076]" box="[189,1036,1437,1464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,313,1438,1464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering from mid-May to mid-June and fruiting June-July.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1401,2076]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,737,1473,1500]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Habitat, distribution, and conservation status</emphasis>
:—The new species occurs on colluvial soils of hillslopes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1154,1176]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1130]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,190,1130]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Nepeta iraqo-iranica sp. nov. A) habitat of plants in Iran, B) habit, C) basal leaves, D) inflorescence, E) close-up of inflorescence in flowering time, F) close-up of inflorescence in fruiting time, G) close-up of corolla, H) nutlets, adaxial (left) and abaxial surface (right). Photographs:A and E, M. Mirtadzadini; B, C, D, F, G and H, K.O.Qader. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641212/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). This species is currently known from two locations 
<quantity box="[750,820,1509,1536]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
apart, one in 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1017,1510,1536]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Iran</collectingCountry>
and the second in 
<collectingCountry box="[1224,1272,1510,1536]" name="Iraq" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, near the border of two countries in Kurdistan region (
<figureCitation box="[572,643,1545,1572]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[183,1399,330,1265]" captionTargetId="figure-76@3.[173,1413,317,1272]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical distribution of Nepeta iraqo-iranica sp. nov. A close-up of the border of Iran and Iraq in the corner. The red circle indicated the locations of N. iraqo-iranica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6641214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6641214/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Further field observations are necessary, but at present by the extent of occurrence (EOO) of about 
<quantity box="[486,580,1581,1607]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.28" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" unit="km" value="6.28">6.28 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[579,587,1581,1595]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">2</superScript>
and the area of occupancy (AOO) of 
<quantity box="[1022,1102,1581,1608]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" unit="km" value="3.8">3.8 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1102,1110,1581,1595]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">2</superScript>
, this species is categorized as “Critically Endangered” (CR) (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[485,630,1618,1644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" refId="ref2961" refString="IUCN (2012) IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, version 3.1, 2 nd edition. IUCN Species Survival Commission. Gland, Switzerland, and Cambridge: International Union for Conservation of Nature." type="book" year="2012">IUCN, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1401,2076]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,390,1653,1680]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
:—The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heinr Braun" authorityYear="1889" box="[761,910,1654,1679]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wettsteinii">
<emphasis box="[761,910,1654,1679]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">N. wettsteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed in 
<collectingRegion box="[1074,1136,1653,1679]" country="Iran" name="Gilan" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Gilan</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1190,1421,1653,1679]" country="Iran" name="Azarbayjan-e Sharqi" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Azerbaijan Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[136,184,1690,1716]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Iran</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hausskneccht &amp; Bornmuller" authorityYear="1899" box="[237,352,1689,1715]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kurdica">
<emphasis box="[237,352,1689,1715]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">N.kurdica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[415,602,1689,1715]" country="Iran" name="Kordestan" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Kurdistan region</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[637,682,1690,1716]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[731,779,1690,1716]" name="Iraq" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, in Group IV (
<bibRefCitation author="Jamzad, Z." box="[931,1081,1689,1716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" pagination="454 - 609" refId="ref3349" refString="Jamzad, Z. (2012) Nepeta. In: Assadi, M., Maassoumi, A. A. &amp; Mozaffarian, V. (Eds.) Flora of Iran, vol. 76. Research Institute of Forests and Rangelands Press, Tehran, pp. 454 - 609. [in Persian]" type="book chapter" year="2012">Jamzad 2012</bibRefCitation>
), in morphological characteristics such as stem indumentum, length of corolla, lower lip margin of corolla, and in the length of calyx exclusively similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heinr Braun" authorityYear="1889" box="[164,311,1762,1787]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wettsteinii">
<emphasis box="[164,311,1762,1787]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">N. wettsteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(The length of calyx according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Jamzad, Z." box="[694,871,1761,1788]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" pagination="454 - 609" refId="ref3349" refString="Jamzad, Z. (2012) Nepeta. In: Assadi, M., Maassoumi, A. A. &amp; Mozaffarian, V. (Eds.) Flora of Iran, vol. 76. Research Institute of Forests and Rangelands Press, Tehran, pp. 454 - 609. [in Persian]" type="book chapter" year="2012">Jamzad (2012))</bibRefCitation>
. But they differ mainly in plant height, size of lower leaf blade, inflorescence shape, length of bract, upper teeth shape of calyx, indumentum of bract and calyx (
<tableCitation box="[1322,1405,1797,1824]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,224,510,536]" captionText="TABLE 1. A comparison of morphological characters of Nepeta iraqo-iranica with N. wettsteinii, N. kurdica, N. humilis and N. petraea." pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Table 1</tableCitation>
). In the new species the inflorescence is compressed and the calyces are not visible. The bracts and their indumentum cover the calyces. While in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hausskneccht &amp; Bornmuller" authorityYear="1899" box="[380,499,1869,1895]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kurdica">
<emphasis box="[380,499,1869,1895]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">N. kurdica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heinr Braun" authorityYear="1889" box="[554,702,1870,1895]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wettsteinii">
<emphasis box="[554,702,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">N. wettsteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the calyces are visible in the inflorescence and can be counted. It should be mentioned that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hausskneccht &amp; Bornmuller" authorityYear="1899" box="[427,545,1905,1931]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kurdica">
<emphasis box="[427,545,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">N. kurdica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heinr Braun" authorityYear="1889" box="[600,748,1906,1931]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wettsteinii">
<emphasis box="[600,748,1906,1931]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">N. wettsteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were considered as synonymous by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rechinger, K. H." box="[1161,1361,1905,1932]" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" pagination="108 - 216" refId="ref3475" refString="Rechinger, K. H. (1982) Nepeta. In: Rechinger, K. H. (Ed.) Flora Iranica, vol. 150. Akademische Druck-und Verlagsanstalt, Graz, pp. 108 - 216." type="book chapter" year="1982">Rechinger (1982)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bordbar &amp; Haloob &amp; Qader &amp; Mirtadzadini" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="iraqo-iranica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Nepeta iraqo-iranica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also compared morphologically to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1848" box="[729,838,1941,1967]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis box="[729,838,1941,1967]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">N.humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1848" box="[890,1001,1942,1967]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Nepeta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="198" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petraea">
<emphasis box="[890,1001,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">N.petraea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the two other sympatric annual species, Group IV, from west of 
<collectingCountry box="[413,458,1978,2004]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Iran</collectingCountry>
and north-east of 
<collectingCountry box="[668,717,1978,2004]" name="Iraq" pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Iraq</collectingCountry>
. The new species can be readily distinguished from them by the difference in shape of lower leaf blade, inflorescence shape, shape and length of bract, length of calyx and corolla (
<tableCitation box="[143,227,2049,2076]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,224,510,536]" captionText="TABLE 1. A comparison of morphological characters of Nepeta iraqo-iranica with N. wettsteinii, N. kurdica, N. humilis and N. petraea." pageId="3" pageNumber="198">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
